



Sir
[c.24 October 1757]



I am strongly importund by Capn Swearengen to place a small Command at Strouds Fort1 if you think it for the Interest of the Service & can possibly spare the Men yr complying Wt. these requests will be agreeable to me Im still off opinion that Dividg yr Command into small Parties will be better than Keepg any No. of them togetherI send you this Inclosd to Capn Swearengen who I have Directed to consult wt. you on the Subject.2
